Defendant Anthony J Langlois in court, in custody, with attorney Jeffrey A. Jaeger.   David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant pleas no contest to both charges as in the Amended Information. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following: as to each count, 

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

9 MONTHS HUBER, w/Standard Release Conditions as to each count consecutive and consecutive to any other sentence

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  any victim or the Alzheimer's Assoc. 
*Letter of apology to Alzheimer's Assoc. (already provided to the DA)
 
RESTITUTION:  $1090.00 to the Alzheimer's Association (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

 COURT COSTS:  $243.00 on each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

 DRGOD Surcharge of $10.00 on each count (to be paid as a condition of probation)
